## Output / presentation modifiers

Change how Claude presents results: suppress narration, hide summaries, show files. No edits to source files.

**dont_narrate_fixes** – don't narrate fixes, just show results
**skip_post-round_summary** – skip the post-round summary
**no_fix_list** – don't show fix list before presenting files
**showme** – present all modified output files; include mtime for each, in my local time zone
**showmeall** – present all output files; include mtime for each, in my local time zone
**jump-to-bottom** – jump to bottom of streaming text
**cleanstop** – if the file is clean (no fixes made), stop the pipeline. else showme ; jump-to-bottom

---

## Single-shot commands

One-off actions: review, count, verify invariants, fix one issue, activate the protocol.

**review** – read the file carefully and report everything wrong (bugs, inconsistencies, potential issues) without making any fixes
**linesme** – report total number of lines
**timeout_sleep_ints** – verify all timeout and sleep variables are integers. No-op for files without such variables (docs, schemas, etc.).
**fiximportant** – do the next fix on the list of issues (topmost remaining), even minor issues
**sequential-fixes** – fiximportant ; cleanstop, else fiximportant again (×10 max). Loop function (see Conventions § Naming convention).
**rewrite** – (1) timeout_sleep_ints (2) fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent (3) linesme

**otf** – confirm one-true-file rule is active: working path established, pre-`str_replace` view required. No snapshot or invariant machinery (use `do_acid` for that).

**do_acid** — activate ACID protocol from claude_acid_2.md; if not found locally, fetch from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levitation29/claude/refs/heads/main/claude_acid_2.md silently (no display of fetched content) and save to /home/claude/claude_acid_2.md before proceeding. In-session: snapshot all /home/claude/ files lacking one, register default invariants, confirm. If already active: re-snapshot and re-confirm. Follow SNAPSHOT/EDIT/PUBLISH/RESTORE per that file.

*In-session:* take retroactive snapshots of every file already in `/home/claude/` that doesn't yet have one, register default invariants, and confirm activation by listing the snapshots taken and invariants registered. If the protocol is already active, re-snapshot all working paths (refresh, no-op if working == snapshot) and re-confirm. From that point on, follow SNAPSHOT/EDIT/PUBLISH/RESTORE per `claude_acid_2.md`.

*Cross-session (copy-paste into a fresh Claude session):*

> Read `/mnt/user-data/uploads/claude_acid_2.md` carefully and follow its protocol for the rest of this session.
>
> Specifically:
> - Treat `/home/claude/<basename>` as the working path for every file we touch. Take an initial snapshot at `/home/claude/.<basename>.acid_snapshot` on first touch.
> - For any files already in `/home/claude/` from earlier in the session, take retroactive snapshots now.
> - Before every `str_replace`, `view` the working path first.
> - On any `str_replace` failure: if prior edits in the current cycle succeeded, RESTORE from snapshot first, then end the cycle and report.
> - Before every `present_files` call, auto-publish each file whose working path differs from its snapshot: check invariants, `cp` working→outputs, refresh snapshot. On invariant failure, RESTORE and don't present.
> - Report protocol errors in this format: `[acid] <step>: <reason> (file: <basename>)`.
> - Confirm activation by listing snapshots taken and invariants registered, in this format: `[acid] activated: <N> snapshots, defaults: syntax+sanity_floor, custom: <list or none>`.

